u053a\u0561\u057c\u0561\u0576\u0563\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0576 \u0561\u057c\u0561\u057e\u0565\u056c \u0568\u0576\u0564\u0563\u056e\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567 \u0561\u0566\u0561\u057f\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576 \u0563\u0561\u0572\u0561\u0583\u0561\u0580\u0576\u0565\u0580\u056b \u056f\u0561\u0580\u0587\u0578\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0568 \u0587 \u0570\u0565\u0576\u0581 \u0561\u0575\u0564 \u0570\u0561\u0574\u0561\u057f\u0565\u0584\u057d\u057f\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567 \u0564\u056b\u057f\u0561\u0580\u056f\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0576\u0561\u0587 \u0561\u0566\u0563\u0561\u0575\u0576\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0563\u0578\u0580\u056e\u0578\u0576\u0576\u0565\u0580\u0568: \u0531\u0575\u057d\u056b\u0576\u0584\u0576` \u0561\u0566\u0563\u0561\u0575\u0576\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u056f\u0578\u0576\u057d\u057f\u0580\u0578\u0582\u056f\u057f\u0568, \u0570\u0561\u0574\u0561\u0571\u0561\u0575\u0576 \u053a\u0561\u057c\u0561\u0576\u0563\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0584\u0561\u0572\u0561\u0584\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576 \u056e\u0580\u0561\u0563\u0580\u056b, \u057a\u0565\u057f\u0584 \u0567 \u056f\u0561\u057c\u0578\u0582\u0581\u057e\u056b \u0561\u0566\u0561\u057f\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0570\u056b\u0574\u0561\u0576 \u057e\u0580\u0561:}}</ref><br>[[Pro-Europeanism]]<ref name=\"about\"/><br>[[Pro-Western]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=de Waal|first1=Thomas|authorlink1=Thomas de Waal|title=The Karabakh trap: Dangers and dilemmas of the Nagorny Karabakh conflict|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/meetdocs/2009_2014/documents/afet/dv/201/201106/20110615_crreport_en.pdf|publisher=[[Conciliation Resources]]|ref=pro-Western Heritage Party|location=London|page=7|date=2011|quote=...pro-Western Heritage Party...}}</ref>\n|position = [[Centrism|Centre]]<ref name=\"coe\"/> to [[centre-right]]\n|international = [[Centrist Democrat International]] (observer)<ref>[https://www.heritage.am/en/news/639-150419-en]</ref>\n|european = [[European People's Party]] (EPP) (observer)<ref>{{cite news|title=Heritage Party on EPP observer status and political corruption in Armenia|url=http://news.am/eng/news/92784.html|accessdate=8 June 2014|newspaper=news.am|date=10 February 2012}}</ref><br>[[European Democratic Party]] (before 2012)<ref name=\"europeanintegration.am\"/>\n|headquarters = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenia]]\n|website = {{url|http://www.heritage.am}}\n|seats1_title = [[National Assembly of Armenia|National Assembly]]\n|seats1 = {{Composition bar|0|132|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n}}\n'''Heritage''' ({{lang-hy|\u053a\u0561\u057c\u0561\u0576\u0563\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576}}, ''Zharangut\u2019yun'') is an [[Armenia]]n [[National liberalism|national liberal]] [[political party|party]]. It was founded in 2002 by [[Raffi Hovannisian]], independent Armenia's first Foreign Minister.\n\n==Policy and ideology==\n;Ideology\n*Support for [[Liberal democracy]].<ref name=\"europeanintegration.am\">{{cite web|title=RA Political Parties: Representation in Europe|url=http://www.europeanintegration.am/en/4246.html|publisher=European Integration NGO|accessdate=8 June 2014|location=Yerevan|quote=Armenian Heritage Party is an advocate of liberal economic and democratic governance system. Despite the party\u2019s declared liberal-democrat ideology it is not a member of ELDR. However, Heritage party that is now in Armenian opposition is also represented in Europe: since recently the Heritage joined the European Democratic Party as an observer.}}</ref>\n\n;Economy\n*[[Economic liberalism]].<ref name=\"europeanintegration.am\"/>\n*\"Domestic policy goals include legal reforms, the development of civil society and the economic development of Armenia. Heritage states that sustaining the competitiveness of the market will help the Armenian economy to grow.\"<ref name=\"europeanforum\"/>\n*\"Furthermore, the party believes that reducing poverty and building good social services are very important for the future of Armenia. By taking these measures, Heritage has the objective to reduce emigration from Armenia and stop the \u201cbrain drain\u201d from the country.\"<ref name=\"europeanforum\"/>\n*The party supports the establishment of a [[Deep and Comprehensive Free Trade Area]] between Armenia and the EU.<ref>[http://www.heritage.am/en/about/election-program?start=14]</ref>\n\n;Foreign Affairs\n*\"Their foreign policy can be characterised as balanced, but also as pro-Western. The Heritage party underlines maintaining and developing good relations with the [[United States]], [[Russia]], [[Georgia (Country)|Georgia]], [[China]] and [[India]], but sees [[European integration]] and cooperation as the key to progress. European integration is not a goal on its own, but rather a tool for improved well-being, prosperity and security. With Turkey, Heritage advocates an open and honest dialogue.\"<ref name=\"europeanforum\">{{cite web|title=Armenia country update|url=http://www.europeanforum.net/country/armenia|publisher=European Forum for Democracy and Solidarity|archivedate=26 June 2014|date=16 January 2014|access-date=8 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626074429/http://www.europeanforum.net/country/armenia|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*The party not only advocates for the [[European integration|integration]] of Armenia with Europe but also the eventual [[Enlargement of the European Union|accession]] of Armenia into the [[European Union]].<ref name=\"about\"/> Heritage firmly believes that for centuries Armenia has been one of the constituents of European civilization, regardless of the geographical boundaries drawn for [[Europe]].<ref>[http://www.heritage.am/hy/about/program?start=8]</ref> The party believes that Armenia must adhere to [[Pan-European identity|Pan-European values]] and that Armenia can contribute to the enrichment of Europe's cultural heritage.\n*Some party members have advocated their support for the withdrawal of Armenia from the [[Collective Security Treaty Organization]].<ref>[https://www.refworld.org/docid/573194744.html]</ref>\n*Recognition of the [[Republic of Artsakh]] as an independent state (the party has several times unsuccessfully proposed bills in the parliament that would formally recognize the NKR by the Republic of Armenia).<ref>{{cite news|title=Karabakh recognition bill put into circulation at Armenian parliament|url=http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/news/121534/|accessdate=28 June 2013|date=4 September 2012|agency=[[PanARMENIAN.Net]]}}</ref>\n*Continued cooperation with both [[NATO]] members and [[Commonwealth of Independent States|CIS]] member states.<ref>[http://www.heritage.am/hy/about/program?start=8]</ref>\n\n==Electoral record==\nThe party emerged as the fifth largest party in the [[National Assembly of Armenia]] after its debut in the [[2007 Armenian parliamentary election]]s. It obtained 7 seats and a popular vote of 5.81%.\n\nFollowing the [[2012 Armenian parliamentary election|2012 parliamentary election]], Heritage won 5 seats by party-list with 86,998 votes, becoming the smallest faction in the Armenian Parliament with [[Zaruhi Postanjyan]] as its leader.<ref>[http://www.parliament.am/deputies.php?sel=factions&lang=eng Factions, National Assembly of the RA]</ref>\n\nHeritage participated in the [[2017 Armenian parliamentary election]] as part of the \"ORO\" Alliance, however the alliance only gained 2.07% of the popular vote, winning no seats.\n\nThe party decided not to participate in the [[2018 Armenian parliamentary election]].\n\n===National Assembly===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:left\"\n|rowspan=2|<center>'''Year'''</center>\n|colspan=3|<center>'''Party-list'''</center>\n|rowspan=2|<center>'''Constituency seats</center>\n|rowspan=2|<center>'''Total seats'''</center>\n|rowspan=2|<center>'''+/\u2013'''</center>\n|-\n|<center>'''Votes'''</center>\n|<center>'''%'''</center>\n|<center>'''Seats/total</center>\n|-\n! [[2007 Armenian parliamentary election|2007]]\n| <center> 81,048</center>\n| <center> 6.0%</center>\n| {{Composition bar|7|90|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|0|41|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|7|131|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}} 7\n|-\n! [[2012 Armenian parliamentary election|2012]]\n| <center> 86,998</center>\n| <center> 5.8%</center>\n| {{Composition bar|5|90|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|0|41|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|5|131|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}} 2\n|-\n! [[2017 Armenian parliamentary election|2017]]\n| <center> 32,508</center>\n| <center> 2.07%</center>\n| {{Composition bar|0|90|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|0|41|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|0|131|hex={{Heritage (Armenia)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}} 5\n|-\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n===President===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:left\"\n|- \n| style=\"width: 20px\"|<center>'''Year'''</center>\n| style=\"width: 150px\"|<center>'''Candidate'''</center>\n| style=\"width: 60px\"|<center>'''Votes'''</center>\n| style=\"width: 20px\"|<center>'''%'''</center>\n| style=\"width: 20px\"|<center>'''Rank'''</center>\n|-\n! [[2008 Armenian presidential election|2008]]\n| colspan=\"4\" |<center>endorsed [[Levon Ter-Petrosyan]]</center>\n|-\n! [[2013 Armenian presidential election|2013]]\n| <center> [[Raffi Hovannisian]]</center>\n| <center> 539,672</center>\n| <center> 36.8%</center>\n| <center> 2</center>\n|-\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Politics}}\n*[[Politics of Armenia]]\n*[[Programs of political parties in Armenia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.heritage.am/ Official website]\n{{Armenian political parties}}\n{{European People's Party}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties in Armenia]]\n[[Category:2002 es